  "riddle": "1. A village in Punjab remains hearbeat of a great tale—locate its coordinates to commence your quest.\n\n2. Ascend from the village by revealing how high it stands above the sea; what elevation does it claim in meters?\n\n3. Nearby shelters scatter like stars—can you count the number of hotels that lie in proximity to your starting point?\n\n4. Combine the height you just discovered with the total accommodations nearby; what sum do you find?\n\n5. Seek knowledge about a distinguished institution of military training located in a city known for its valleys; what elevation does it boast?\n\n6. Amongst its hallowed halls, cadets from various lands gather; how many nations send their future leaders to learn there?\n\n7. Of the number you found in clue 6, what is the count of its divisors? \n\n8. Shift your gaze to a region steeped in history; what is the total number of inhabitants dwelling in Pakistan as recorded today?\n\n9. From your count in clue 8, ascertain the next prime number that follows it; what do you uncover?\n\n10. The place where brave souls are molded into warriors lies at a central command—can you name this location?\n\n11. Journey to Abbottabad, where the air is crisp. What altitude does this place reach above sea level?\n\n12. Museums bear witness to the past around Abbottabad; how many can be found within a short distance of this town?\n\n13. Take the elevation from clue 11, and measure it against the number of museums found in clue 12. What is the absolute difference?\n\n14. Turn now to a land rich with diversity; what is the population count of India as recorded in modern times?\n\n15. Discover the command center of the Pakistan Army; where does this headquarters lay — can you describe its location?\n\n16. Gather the results of clues 3 and 9 and find the digital root of their sum, expressed as: digital_root(clue 3 + clue 9). Reveal your final answer, a single digit between 0 and 9.",
